## New Project: docket
- **Replaces:** node-schedule (3.4M weekly npm downloads, 2,116 dependents, 9.2k stars, last feature commit Nov 2021, last npm release 3+ years ago, 154 open issues, single inactive maintainer)
- **Why:** Massive usage. Effectively unmaintained since 2021. No drop-in replacement — node-cron is cron-only, Bree/BullMQ are much heavier with different paradigms.
- **Package:** @agentine/docket (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** scheduleJob(), cancelJob(), scheduledJobs, gracefulShutdown(), RecurrenceRule, Range, Job (EventEmitter), Invocation, cron 5/6-field parsing, Date scheduling, IANA timezone support. Zero dependencies, TypeScript-first, ESM+CJS.
- **Compat layer:** docket/compat/node-schedule (drop-in module replacement for `import schedule from 'node-schedule'`)
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #809 (scaffolding), #810 (cron parser), #811 (RecurrenceRule), #812 (Job + Scheduler), #813 (compat layer + tests)

